<p>When entering a critical section the program holds a lock that can be hold by a single entity at a time. It is then recommended that the critical
section is reduced to the minimum required and executed without any interruption.</p>
<h2>Noncompliant Code Example</h2>
<pre>
void f() {
  std::mutex m;
  // ...
  m.lock();
  // ...
  sleep(1); // Noncompliant
  // ...
  m.unlock();
}
</pre>